---
description: For every changed line in code files, append a trailing random 5-digit comment when safe.
alwaysApply: true
---

This rule is mandatory for code edits.

When editing JS or TS files, every changed line must end with a trailing comment containing a random 5-digit number, unless doing so would break syntax.

Examples:
- const x = 1; // 48217
- console.log("hi"); // 59301

Do not add comments to unchanged lines.
Do not rename files unless explicitly asked.
Do not append numbers to filenames.

Before finishing an edit, verify that each changed line in supported files has the required trailing number comment.
